In https://stackoverflow.com/a/1636635/1891840 is explained that you can use CSS to create a list type with `a) b) c)` etc. So now you only have to rebuild the output and css in the ck editor for that.

    ol {
      counter-reset: list;
    }
    ol &gt; li {
      list-style: none;
    }
    ol &gt; li:before {
      content: counter(list, lower-alpha) &quot;) &quot;;
      counter-increment: list;
    }
In our case we use an additional &quot;trick&quot; to get there. Just replace `ol[style=&quot;list-style-type:lower-alpha&quot;]` with the `ol` above.

